<h2>How to access network shares</h2>

<p>
    Roms and configs are stored on your Retropie/Recalbox installation, and are accessible
    through network shares. This app allows to directly write on these shares.
</p>

<h3>Windows</h3>

<p>
    On Windows, you can access the shares very simply:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>Roms: <strong>\\retropie\roms</strong> or <strong>\\recalbox\\roms</strong></li>
    <li>Configs: <strong>\\retropie\configs</strong> or <strong>\\recalbox\share\system\configs</strong></li>
</ul>

<h3>MacOS</h3>

<p>
    On MacOS, first you have to mount the Samba shares.
</p>
<ol>
    <li>Open a Finder window, then select menu <strong>Go &gt; Connect to server</strong></li>
    <li>Enter: <strong>smb://retropie/</strong> or <strong>smb://recalbox/</strong></li>
    <li>When asked for a password, connect as guest</li>
    <li>Select the folder(s) you wish to mount</li>
</ol>
<p>
    Once the folder is mounted, you can access through <strong>/Volumes/name_of_share</strong>
</p>

<h3>Linux</h3>

<p>
    Mounting a network share depends on your Linux distribution, and
    tends to change from version to version. Using the "browse" buttons
    is probably the easiest way.
</p>